Trying another way apart from what was stated in the SE website.

Add command currently makes the -nn tag compulsory, if not mistaken. For
empty nicknames, the GUI shows them as an empty line below the email. To
allow nicknames to be optional when writing the add command, and for the
nickname component to only be shown if the nickname is not an empty
String, let's

* Change the nickname component in fxml file as a FlowPane rather than a
  Label
* Change the code in AddCommandParser.java where
  arMultimap.getValue(PREFIX_NICKNAME).orElse("") rather than .get() so
  that an empty Optional object returned will be seen as a empty String
  return to alow for parsing in parseNickname function

This are the main changes to allow nickname to be an optional
requirement in Add Command.

Errors occur due to nickname field being missing in the creation of
Perosn object. Edit it to include nickname field (psudo-optional for
now).

commitResults.messageBody:
All roles are rendered as blue labels in UI.

Different colors allows users to identify different contacts with
different roles easier.

A private method getRoleLabel is added to set id of the label
corresponding to its role name. Different colors are added in DarkTheme
.css to apply on labels with different ids.

A label needs to be associated with an id in order for CSS selectors to
locate the element. Hence, each role name needs to be mapped to an id.
